First we locate 2026 on the hexagonal spiral.  
Let a hexagon have a “radius” \(r\) defined by  

\[
r=\max \bigl(|x|,\;|y|,\;|z|\bigr),\qquad (x,y,z)\text{ cube coordinates}
\]

For a ring of radius \(r\)

\[
\text{previous total}=1+3(r-1)r ,\qquad 
\text{start}=\,\text{previous total}+1 .
\]

The cells of a ring are traversed in six directions  
\(d_0=(1,0, -1), d_1=(1,-1,0), d_2=(0,-1,1),
 d_3=(-1,0,1), d_4=(-1,1,0), d_5=(0,1,-1).\)

The offsets inside a ring are

\[
\text{offset}=2r+(r-1)-z\quad\text{when }x=-r,
\]

\(z\) being the “r” coordinate of the cell.

---

### 1.  Locate 2026  

Solve

\[
1+3(r-1)r < 2026 \le 1+3r(r+1)
\]

which gives \(r=26\).
The beginning of ring 26 is at number \(1952\).

The offset of 2026 is

\[
\text{offset}=2026-1952=74 .
\]

With \(r=26\) this corresponds to the cube coordinate \((-26,3)\).

---

### 2.  Neighbour coordinates of \((-26,3)\)

Adding the six step directions gives

| Direction | Coordinate |
|-----------|------------|
| \(d_0=(1,0)\) | \((-25,3)\) |
| \(d_1=(1,-1)\) | \((-26,4)\) |
| \(d_2=(0,-1)\) | \((-27,4)\) |
| \(d_3=(-1,0)\) | \((-27,3)\) |
| \(d_4=(-1,1)\) | \((-26,2)\) |
| \(d_5=(0,1)\) | \((-25,2)\) |

---

### 3.  Numbers of the neighbors  

For each coordinate we determine its radius \(r\), the start number of that ring and the offset inside that ring using the rule above.

| Coordinate | \(r\) | start | offset | number |
|------------|-------|-------|--------|--------|
| \((-25,3)\) | 25 | 1802 | 71 | **1873** |
| \((-26,4)\) | 26 | 1952 | 73 | **2025** |
| \((-27,4)\) | 27 | 2108 | 76 | **2184** |
| \((-27,3)\) | 27 | 2108 | 77 | **2185** |
| \((-26,2)\) | 26 | 1952 | 75 | **2027** |
| \((-25,2)\) | 25 | 1802 | 72 | **1874** |

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbors  

\[
\text{Sum}=1873+2025+2184+2185+2027+1874
= 12\,168 .
\]

\[
\boxed{12\,168}
\]
